data.current_description: Gets the layer summary for a volume.
data.summary_suggestion: Get a specific layer summary for a volume
data.description_suggestion: Retrieves the detailed layer summary for a specific layer within a volume. Layers represent different types of annotations and metadata overlays on a book (such as dictionary definitions, citations, or user annotations). Requires both volumeId and summaryId parameters to identify the target layer. Returns a layer summary object containing metadata about the layer including its ID, name, content type, update information, and availability status. Use this operation to fetch details about a particular annotation layer before accessing its full content.
